# quicknote-cli

A small, single-file Python CLI app for taking quick notes (TODOs / snippets) and storing them locally in JSON. Ready to drop into a GitHub repository.

---

## Repo structure

```
quicknote-cli/
├── README.md
├── quicknote.py
├── .gitignore
└── LICENSE
```

---

## README.md

````markdown
# QuickNote CLI

QuickNote CLI is a tiny command-line tool for adding, listing, removing, and searching short notes or todos. It stores data locally in `~/.quicknote.json`.

## Requirements
- Python 3.8+

## Install
Clone the repo and (optionally) copy `quicknote.py` to somewhere on your PATH, or run with Python:

```bash
python quicknote.py add "Buy milk"
````

## Usage

```text
Usage: quicknote.py <command> [options]

Commands:
  add "text"        Add a new note
  list               List all notes
  remove <id>        Remove note by id
  search "term"     Search notes containing term
  clear              Remove all notes (confirmation required)
  export <file>      Export notes as JSON to file
```

